newsitem.title: MEXICO: Uruguay president starts visit to Mexico.
newsitem.headline: Uruguay president starts visit to Mexico.

text.p: Uruguay's President Julio Maria Sanguinetti arrived in Mexico on Tuesday for a five-day visit during which he was expected to promote closer economic and political ties among Latin American nations.
Sanguinetti, travelling with a team of ministers and businessmen, was scheduled to meet President Ernesto Zedillo on Wednesday and will also meet political and business leaders.
Zedillo and Sanguinetti were also expected to sign an accord on extradition between their countries, diplomatic sources said.
Uruguay is a member of the Mercosur trade zone with Argentina, Brazil and Paraguay while Mexico is a member of the North American Free Trade Agreement with Canada and the United States.
